public interface InkObject
extends Proxiable

The interface of the base Ink behavior object. Every behavior object in Ink implements this interface (explicitly or via inheritance).

Author:
Lior Schachter
See Also:

Method Detail

afterStateSet

void afterStateSet()
A hook method, notifying the behavior object that the state object has been created (or modified externally). This method is a rough equivalent of a constructor method in Java. However, note that it may be invoked multiple times during the lifecycle of a behavior object: when a behavior is first created and injected with its state object, and after the state object has been modified (e.g. by an ObjectEditor).
This method should contain initialization logic of the behavior object.

cloneState

<T extends InkObjectState> T cloneState()
Creates a deep clone of this behavior object's state. The clone operation traverses the state object and creates a clone of every mutable object it encounters, such as inner state objects and collections. (Primitive values are immutable and therefore are shallow-copied.)
Object IDs are not cloned. The cloned state object and all its inner objects have unique IDs. Behavior objects are not created during this operation.

Returns:
a deep clone of this behavior object's state.

validate

boolean validate(ValidationContext context,
                 SystemState systemState)
Validates this object by executing the validators from the constraints trait relevant to the required system state. The messages reported during validation are collected into the context object.

Parameters:
context - a ValidationContext object into which the validation messages are collected.
systemState - denotes whether design-time or run-time validators should be invoked.
Returns:
true if no validation errors were encountered, false otherwise.
See Also:
Validator, InstanceValidator.validate(InkObjectState, org.ink.core.vm.mirror.Mirror, ValidationContext, SystemState), PropertyValueValidator.validate(Property, Object, InkObjectState, ValidationContext, SystemState)

validate

boolean validate(ValidationContext context)
Validates this object by executing the validators from the constraints trait relevant to run-time system state. Equivalent to calling validate(context, SystemState.Run_Time). The messages reported during validation are collected into the context object.

Parameters:
context - a ValidationContext object into which the validation messages are collected.
Returns:
true if no validation errors were encountered, false otherwise.
See Also:
Validator, InstanceValidator.validate(InkObjectState, org.ink.core.vm.mirror.Mirror, ValidationContext, SystemState), PropertyValueValidator.validate(Property, Object, InkObjectState, ValidationContext, SystemState)
